	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />i'm not taking about making samples for DPCM, i'm talking about recording output from the NES
<br />
<br />I know people have been wondering things like that is the frequency response of the nes hardware, what kind of noise the PPU adds to the signal, etc.  this is a chance to record the nes output without worrying about contamination in the recording chain 
<br />
<br />i know there are already a few demo which test various audio capabilities.. i was just wondering if people wanted to make some more and have me record them

		

		</td>
	</tr>
