	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I can't think of any hardware tests that would benefit from a low-noise high-resolution sampler. All the measurements we're interested in are much more coarse than that. The worst contamination you'll get is the PPU's video signal, followed perhaps by the 60 Hz hum of the power transformer.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
